Place pecans in microwaveable pie plate sprayed with cooking spray. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar; toss to coat. Spread evenly onto bottom of pie plate. Microwave on HIGH 1 to 1-1/2 min. or until toasted, stirring every 30 sec. Meanwhile, toss greens with pears, cheese and cranberries in large bowl. Add pecans and dressing just before serving; mix lightly.